# Project Grow-Cold Global Rules

# GrowCold — Cursor Rules

## Perosna
You are a Senior Full-Stack Engineer for mobile apps

## Project
Mobile-first WMS for Indian cold-storage SMBs. Stack: Expo + React Native + GlueStack UI + Supabase.
Every decision must pass: "Will a 50-yr-old warehouse owner in rural AP use this without help?"

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- Functional components only, no class components
- Zod for all input validation (forms + API boundaries)
- TanStack Query for all server state; no raw fetch/useEffect for data fetching
- Named exports for components, default exports for screens/pages
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Collocate component styles — no global CSS unless it's a design token

## File Structure
```
apps/
  mobile/          # Expo app
    src/
      screens/     # One file per screen
      components/  # Shared UI
      hooks/       # Custom hooks (useStock, useSync, etc.)
      stores/      # Zustand stores for offline queue
      i18n/        # Translation files per language
  web/             # React + Vite
packages/
  supabase/        # DB types, RLS policies, migrations
  shared/          # Zod schemas, utils, constants shared across apps
```

## Supabase Rules
- All tables must have RLS enabled — warehouse_id is the tenant key
- Use generated TypeScript types from Supabase CLI (`supabase gen types`)
- Realtime subscriptions only for online-aware UI — never block core ops on it
- Auth: phone number only, no email fields in any form
- Storage buckets: scoped per warehouse_id path

## Offline-First Pattern
```ts
// Always: write to local queue first, then sync
async function recordInward(entry: InwardEntry) {
  await localQueue.push(entry);           // immediate, offline-safe
  triggerSync();                          // async, non-blocking
}
```
- Use `expo-sqlite` for local storage on mobile
- Conflict resolution: last-write-wins by `updated_at` timestamp (keep it simple)
- Sync status always visible to user (pending badge count)

## UI / UX Rules
- GlueStack UI components only — no raw RN primitives unless unavoidable
- Every action must have haptic feedback (`expo-haptics`)
- Use skeleton screens — never blank loading states
- Optimistic updates: update UI before API confirms
- No modals for primary actions — use full screens or bottom sheets
- Minimum touch target: 48x48px
- All user-facing strings go through i18n — no hardcoded English text

## i18n
- Default language: Telugu (`te`) for onboarding flows; detect via `expo-localization`
- Translation keys: `namespace.screen.element` (e.g., `inward.form.quantity_label`)
- Currency: always format with `Intl.NumberFormat('en-IN')` — lakhs/crores
- Dates: DD/MM/YYYY always

## What Not to Do
- No complex multi-step wizards for core ops (inward/outward must be ≤3 taps)
- No features that require internet for core workflows
- No SKU/ERP/WMS jargon in UI strings
- No email-based auth flows
- No client-side secrets — all sensitive ops via Supabase Edge Functions
- Don't add a feature without a clear user story tied to the 50-yr-old owner persona

## Naming Conventions
| Concept | Code name |
|---------|-----------|
| Inventory entry in | `inward` or `lodgement`|
| Inventory entry out | `outward` or `delivery`|
| Customer/Supplier | `party` |
| Product group | `product` or `product-group` |
| Warehouse | `warehouse` (not `facility`) |

## PR / Commit Standards
- Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:` prefixes
- Every PR must include: what changed, why, how to test offline scenario
- Flag any change that adds a new Supabase table — needs RLS review

## Performance Targets
- Core screens: <2s on 3G
- Offline queue: handle 500+ pending transactions
- Product list: paginate beyond 100 items — never load all
